Today was a short-ish hike at Watkins Glen State Park in New York.  I had seen photos before, but never been.  Absolutely must see!  Stay at the State Park campground (great location!) and then head on into the park for some hiking and photos.  If you've not been, add it to your list.  This is a picture looking through a tunnel at a waterfall that you  can walk behind.  The path is manmade, but the waterfall itself is not.
